  "abstract": "To collect and harvest rain water mud is as good as stone, and more cost-effective too. These\r\nare the findings of a study carried out in the integrated watershed program undertaken by a\r\nconsortium of partners, led by ICRISAT, in three states of India.In India, through various watershed programs, heavy investments are being made in the\r\nconstruction of groundwater recharging structures for improving the groundwater resources.\r\nCurrently, masonry type structures are constructed in the watershed programs, which are\r\nexpensive and difficult to maintain.\r\nc\r\n",
